704844f-a.text:
Henry Street, north from Joralemon Street. The second car is at Hunt's Alley. In the distance on the right, is the Church of the Pilgrim's. The 4 1/2 story building at the right, was Hunt's Mansion built in 1868, of
Brownstone and Brick.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Views 2 & 3: April 5, 1938.

705153f-a.text:
Joralemon Street, west from Henry Street.  No. 107 is at the extreme right.  (In 1838 the "Osceola Rowing Club" had its boathouse at the foot of Joralemon Street, then known as Joralemon Lane; and the Eagle Tavern was nearby.)

About 1919.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
